entry.def: A dugout is a shelter made by digging a hole in the ground and then covering it or tunnelling so that the shelter has a roof over it.

means.word_mean: 1. either of two low shelters on either side of a baseball diamond where the players and coaches sit during the game
2. a canoe made by hollowing out and shaping a large log
3. a fortification of earth; mostly or entirely below ground
